<div id="review_680300781" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/680300781" />
    <a title="Meredith DeVoe" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15945671-meredith-devoe"><img alt="Meredith DeVoe" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1357053303p2/15945671.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/680300781?book_show_action=true">Jul 29, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Meredith DeVoe" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Meredith DeVoe" href="/user/show/15945671-meredith-devoe">Meredith DeVoe</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer680300781" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5037182033439769991">This is a life-changing book, if you really take what it teaches to heart. When a friend presented the book to me (10 years ago), my first thought was &quot;But I&apos;m not really anxious.&quot; The book really focuses on contentment-- contentment with your life, yourself, your family, your circumstances. I learned to trust God on a deeper level by working through this book and the Scriptures she uses abundantly. Ten years later, this is still a go-to book for me. As a missionary in Nigeria, opportunities for</span>
  <span id="freeText5037182033439769991" style="display:none">This is a life-changing book, if you really take what it teaches to heart. When a friend presented the book to me (10 years ago), my first thought was "But I'm not really anxious." The book really focuses on contentment-- contentment with your life, yourself, your family, your circumstances. I learned to trust God on a deeper level by working through this book and the Scriptures she uses abundantly. Ten years later, this is still a go-to book for me. As a missionary in Nigeria, opportunities for anxiety and discontent abound! This book returns me to truths of God's sufficiency and faithfulness. I need that. HIGHEST RECOMMENDATION for anyone who is unhappy, irritated, frustrated with their life, as I was (and admittedly still am sometimes. God isn't through with me yet!!). </span>
  <a data-text-id="5037182033439769991" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


