<div id="review_2176391166" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2176391166" />
    <a title="Ashley Owens" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/546428-ashley-owens"><img alt="Ashley Owens" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1467642516p2/546428.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2176391166?book_show_action=true">Nov 07, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ashley Owens" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ashley Owens" href="/user/show/546428-ashley-owens">Ashley Owens</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2176391166" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17689685069950764624">This book reminds us to give our anxieties to God, sometimes easier said than done. But the author does a good job of putting our innate need to control into perspective: <br/>“It was as if I were sitting in the back seat of a Land Rover in a little car seat that had its own steering wheel. I was turning the wheel left, then right, but I never realized that my steering wheel wasn’t connected to anything. One day I looked up and realized that I wasn’t the one driving.”</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review2176391166">
