  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4442263198?book_show_action=true">Jan 03, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Emily Uhlmeyer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Emily Uhlmeyer" href="/user/show/31886242-emily-uhlmeyer">Emily Uhlmeyer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4442263198" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer722517457341705539">This book is practical and personal, convicting and encouraging. The author shares stories both from her life and the lives of others as though you’re chatting over a cup of coffee. The call throughout is to an eternal perspective, with eyes fixed and situations surrendered to the Blessed Controller of all things. Calm My Anxious Heart is relatable and written with graciousness and understanding, complete with a twelve week study guide to practically apply the principles shared. What a hard but </span>
  <span id="freeText722517457341705539" style="display:none">This book is practical and personal, convicting and encouraging. The author shares stories both from her life and the lives of others as though you’re chatting over a cup of coffee. The call throughout is to an eternal perspective, with eyes fixed and situations surrendered to the Blessed Controller of all things. Calm My Anxious Heart is relatable and written with graciousness and understanding, complete with a twelve week study guide to practically apply the principles shared. What a hard but beautiful thing it is to be content with what the Lord gives, trusting Him for a calm and steadfast heart. This will be book I reference and re-read often!</span>
  <a data-text-id="722517457341705539" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


