  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_154304703" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/154304703" />
    <a title="Amanda" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2773888-amanda"><img alt="Amanda" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1557492442p2/2773888.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/154304703?book_show_action=true">Mar 14, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amanda" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amanda" href="/user/show/2773888-amanda">Amanda</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/10726247-calm-my-anxious-heart">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer154304703&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer154304703" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer890581271952393738">I struggle a bit with separation anxiety and the fear of someone I love becoming ill or dying (morbid, huh?), so I read this book to see if it would provide me with any insight on how to deal with my anxiousness. I read the book as part of my regular Bible study and devotional time and I enjoyed it. The book contains story after story about women who chose to be content with their circumstances and refused to worry about things out of their control. Calm My Anxious Heart is a good refresher for </span>
  <span id="freeText890581271952393738" style="display:none">I struggle a bit with separation anxiety and the fear of someone I love becoming ill or dying (morbid, huh?), so I read this book to see if it would provide me with any insight on how to deal with my anxiousness. I read the book as part of my regular Bible study and devotional time and I enjoyed it. The book contains story after story about women who chose to be content with their circumstances and refused to worry about things out of their control. Calm My Anxious Heart is a good refresher for someone looking to be reminded of the life God calls Christians to live. I have included some of my favorite quotes from the book below. My "favorite favorite" of them all is the last one. :)<br /><br />- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -<br /><br />"What we are on the inside, what we continually think about, eventually shows in our words, actions, and even on our countenances." (Kindle Location 123-124)<br /><br />"An eternal perspective, then, is God's way of seeing. When we have God's perspective, we view our lives and evaluate what is important from His viewpoint." (Kindle Location 139-140)<br /><br />"Most of us base our contentment on our circumstances, on our feelings, or on other people. However, true contentment is separate from our circumstances. Contentment is a state of the heart, not a state of affairs." (Kindle Location 160-161)<br /><br />"Paul recognized that the source and strength of all Christian contentment is God Himself." (Kindle Location 182)<br /><br />"How does God enable us to be content? He infuses contentment into us through His Word. As it seeps into our minds, it transforms us. Just as a cup of tea gets stronger when we give it time to steep, so we become more content when we spend time in God's Word and allow it to seep into our lives, transforming us o be like Him." (Kindle Location 188-191)<br /><br />"It's our 'helping God out' that leads to an anxious heart. When we take our focus off the One who is in control and put our eyes on our circumstances." (Kindle Location 202-203)<br /><br />"Contentment is essentially a matter of accepting from God's hand what He sends because we know that He is good and therefore it is good." (Kindle Location 208-209)<br /><br />"Our anxiety should be used as a springboard to pray specifically. Our part in the process of learning to be content is a heart choice - a choice to pray rather than be anxious." (Kindle Location 341-342)<br /><br />"When confronted with negative circumstances, we have a choice: Will we pray about the problem or will we worry about it?" (Kindle Location 354-355)<br /><br />"If we make the choice to pray instead of worry, we will personally experience god's peace." (Kindle Location 358)<br /><br />"When anxieties multiply within me, my mind goes absolutely crazy with 'what ifs.' My heart, the cradle of my emotions rocks wildly back and forth. God's peace is the exact prescription needed for my anxiety-ridden heart and mind." (Kindle Location 363-365)<br /><br />"The Proverbs 31 woman was not controlled by her circumstances and the demands of her family, her household, or her home business. She was ruler of her attitudes, her time, and her schedule. Her relationship with God was central. All that she became was a result of her yielding to His sovereign control." (Kindle Location 598-600)<br /><br />"When we were in school, we couldn't wait to be adults so we could do whatever we wanted. When, exactly, does that start? … We grow up when we see our life and our role from God's perspective; when we thank God for the role He has assigned us and begin to see our cup as a gift instead of a cross; when each morning we ask, 'God, how can I glorify You today in my given role?" (Kindle Location 726-731)<br /><br />"Worry doesn't empty tomorrow if its sorrow, it empties today of its strength." (Kindle Location 1558-1559)<br /><br />- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -<br /><br />This book was free on the Amazon Kindle when I downloaded it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="890581271952393738" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


