<div id="review_26939330" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/26939330" />
    <a title="Stacey" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/731014-stacey"><img alt="Stacey" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1203713958p2/731014.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/26939330?book_show_action=true">Jul 11, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stacey" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stacey" href="/user/show/731014-stacey">Stacey</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">women</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Stacey by: </span>
      Jorene
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/731014-stacey?shelf=faith">faith</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/731014-stacey?shelf=kindle">kindle</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer26939330" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6969803759268382293">rereading this treasure...pertinent to my current challenges...<br/><br/>***<br/><br/>I really loved this book. When my friend Jorene lent it to me, I dug right in. Then, I found it at a yard sale for a quarter. Once I owned it, it became less of a priority (why is that?).<br/><br/>ANyway, it has really blessed me these last few days. I particularly enjoyed most of it-- but since that is not very helpful... I enjoyed the chapter on faulty focus as the author shared a few &quot;mature women&apos;s&quot; stories on how they set their course,</span>
  <span id="freeText6969803759268382293" style="display:none">rereading this treasure...pertinent to my current challenges...<br /><br />***<br /><br />I really loved this book. When my friend Jorene lent it to me, I dug right in. Then, I found it at a yard sale for a quarter. Once I owned it, it became less of a priority (why is that?).<br /><br />ANyway, it has really blessed me these last few days. I particularly enjoyed most of it-- but since that is not very helpful... I enjoyed the chapter on faulty focus as the author shared a few "mature women's" stories on how they set their course, and focus their lives intentionally. I also found that I read up to that point twice and put it down, intending to spend some time deliberately plotting my own spiritual course-- but mainly the book just gathered some dust-- but it was for such a time as this the book resurfaced. And some of the nuggets that spoke to me, were also meant for a good friend of mine that I shared them with. God loves her so much, he reminded me of this book.<br /><br />I also liked the clarification that depression is about living in the past, and anxiety is living in the future, but God's will for us is in today.<br /><br />and<br /><br />"Life is full of potential problems and pain. But we have a choice. We can worry or we can trust the Trustworothy One."<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6969803759268382293" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


